<article>
    <h1>EN&#xAD;JOY&#xAD;ABLE WAIT&#xAD;ING TIMES</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210109/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-09"><time>2021-01-09</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Wait­ing time need not be a bore for chil­dren, with na­ture-themed re­cep­tion ar­eas spread out over three floors and ad­ja­cent out­door play­grounds.</p>
    <p>The in­sti­tute’s com­mu­nity part­ners have helped en­hance the de­sign fur­ther.</p>
    <p>In­ter­ac­tive ed­u­ca­tional ex­hibits cu­rated by the Sci­ence Cen­tre Sin­ga­pore are placed across the wait­ing ar­eas to en­gage chil­dren.</p>
    <p>Sub­tle scents cre­ated by fra­grance house Gi­vau­dan com­ple­ment the rain­for­est, sa­van­nah and arc­tic themes of the three floors where the con­sul­ta­tion rooms are lo­cated.</p>
    <p>The in­sti­tute is also working with Wildlife Re­serves Sin­ga­pore on in­for­ma­tion boards for the wall mu­rals across three con­sul­ta­tion floors. The boards will fea­ture var­i­ous an­i­mals to en­cour­age learn­ing and in­spire care for wildlife.</p>
    <p>On Level 6, a cheery rain­for­est theme greets pa­tients with lots of greens and yel­lows on the wall­pa­per and match­ing fur­ni­ture up­hol­stery.</p>
    <p>On Level 7, the colours be­come warmer, with rus­tic browns and or­ange on the walls, tree­house de­signs around the nurses’ sta­tions and im­ages of wild an­i­mals such as gi­raffes and ze­bras.</p>
    <p>It be­comes cooler one floor up on Level 8, where the re­cep­tion area fea­tures an arc­tic theme with cool blues and creams, and po­lar bears on the walls.</p>
    <p>The de­sign also al­lows chil­dren to climb, in­ter­act and ex­plore the dif­fer­ent themes un­der the watch­ful eye of care­givers.</p>

